''' word bank 
The ________ function lets you display your list in a particular order, but doesnâ€™t affect the actual order of the list.  sorted()
A ____ is a collection of items in a particular order.                                                                    list
The ______ method changes the order of the list permanently.                                                              .sorted()
You can access any element in a list by telling Python the position, or _____, of the item desired.                       index
You can quickly find the length of a list by using the _____ function.                                                    len()
List method used to add an element to the end of a list.                                                                  .append()
List method used to insert an element at any position in a list.                                                          .insert()
If you know the position of the item you want to remove from a list, you can use the ___ statement.                         del 
If you only know the value of the item you want to remove, you can use the ________ method.                               .remove()
Method used to remove item from any position in a list and then use that value after it has been removed.                   .pop()
'''

#organizing the list with sort()
genres = ['edm', 'rock', 'rap', 'indie', 'jazz']
genres.sort()
genres

genres = ['edm', 'rock', 'rap', 'indie', 'jazz']
print(sorted(genres))
print(genres)
#printing without sorted

#permanently print with sorted order, reverse(), this is a method !!!!!
genres = ['edm', 'rock', 'rap', 'indie', 'jazz']
genres.reverse()
genres

#length (how many variables are in the list)
len(genres)

